      "text": "Thereby, there are always preliminary performances to be made, which seligize sense references and condense them to a contradiction; but only if these preliminary performances are unified to a form, logical conditioning can take effect, above all the conditioning by a general rule of avoiding contradictions. The form of the contradiction results only from the totality of its uses in logic. It need not be assumed historically invariant, but it can be thought that it varies with the kind of its social use."
